title: Watch: Joseph Masi's 60-second Walsall update - October 12
text:
Be the first to comment 
The result, in front of almost 7,000 fans at the Banks’s Stadium, allowed Smith’s side to leapfrog their opponents and move back to the top of the League One. 
They have 25 points from their opening 12 games but, despite another fine team performance, the Walsall boss is remaining calm with just a quarter of the season having been played. Receive daily email updates from the Express & Star
